{"questionId":"9466","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>This question asks you to investigate regular <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n</math></span>-sided polygons inscribed and circumscribed&nbsp;in a circle, and the perimeter of these as <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n</math></span> tends to infinity, to make an approximation for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\pi \">\n  <mi>π</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{P_i}\\left( n \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>P</mi>\n      <mi>i</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>n</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> represent the perimeter of any <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n</math></span>-sided regular polygon inscribed in a circle of&nbsp;radius 1 unit.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider an equilateral triangle ABC of side length, <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> units, circumscribed about a circle of&nbsp;radius 1 unit and centre O as shown in the following diagram.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/300c0ddb02b59d7560ae1722763f5b7c11cabf5a.png\"></p>\n<p>Let <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{P_c}\\left( n \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>P</mi>\n      <mi>c</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>n</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> represent the perimeter of any <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n\">\n  <mi>n</mi>\n</math></span>-sided regular polygon circumscribed about a&nbsp;circle of radius 1 unit.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Use the results from part (d) and part (f) to determine an inequality for the value of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\pi \"> <mi>π</mi> </math></span> in&nbsp;terms of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n\"> <mi>n</mi> </math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{P_i} < 2\\pi&nbsp; < {P_c}\"> <mrow> <msub> <mi>P</mi> <mi>i</mi> </msub> </mrow> <mo>&lt;</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mi>π</mi> <mo>&lt;</mo> <mrow> <msub> <mi>P</mi> <mi>c</mi> </msub> </mrow> </math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2n\\,{\\text{sin}}\\left( {\\frac{\\pi }{n}} \\right) < 2\\pi&nbsp; < 2n\\,{\\text{tan}}\\left( {\\frac{\\pi }{n}} \\right)\"> <mn>2</mn> <mi>n</mi> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mrow> <mtext>sin</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mfrac> <mi>π</mi> <mi>n</mi> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>&lt;</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mi>π</mi> <mo>&lt;</mo> <mn>2</mn> <mi>n</mi> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mrow> <mtext>tan</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mfrac> <mi>π</mi> <mi>n</mi> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"n\\,{\\text{sin}}\\left( {\\frac{\\pi }{n}} \\right) < \\pi&nbsp; < n\\,{\\text{tan}}\\left( {\\frac{\\pi }{n}} \\right)\"> <mi>n</mi> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mrow> <mtext>sin</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mfrac> <mi>π</mi> <mi>n</mi> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> <mo>&lt;</mo> <mi>π</mi> <mo>&lt;</mo> <mi>n</mi> <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace> <mrow> <mtext>tan</mtext> </mrow> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mfrac> <mi>π</mi> <mi>n</mi> </mfrac> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9466","referenceCode":"SPM.3.AHL.TZ0.1h","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Use the results from part (d) and part (f) to determine an inequality for the value of π in terms of n .","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"h","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.13—Limits and L’Hopitals","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.19—Maclaurin series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}